kandarian president chairman and ceo products insurance annuities employee benefits revenue us billion f operating income us billion  us billion f net income us billion f total assets us billion f us billion f total equity us billion f number of employees   website metlifecom metlife inc is the holding corporation for the metropolitan life insurance company mlic better known as metlife and its affiliates metlife is among the largest global providers of insurance annuities and employee benefit programs with  million customers in over  countries the firm was founded on march   on january   metlife completed the mutualization process changing from a stock life insurance company owned by individuals to a mutual company operating without external shareholders and for the benefit of policyholders the company went public in  through its subsidiaries and affiliates metlife holds leading market positions in the united states japan latin america asia’s pacific region europe and the middle east metlife serves  of the largest fortune  companies the company’s principal offices are located at  park avenue new york city in midtown manhattan new york city though it retains some executive offices and its boardroom in the metlife building located at  park avenue new york city which it sold in  in january  the company announced that it would spin off us retail business including individual life insurance and annuities for the retail market in a separate company called brighthouse financial they will maintain the metlife name on metlife stadium on march   the separated us retail business launched brighthouse financial – an independent company focused on life insurance and annuities contents  corporate structure  corporate governance  subsidiary and affiliate companies  history  early years  postwar  demutualization and ipo  acquisitions sales and major deals  current era  too big to fail  fines  products and services  life insurance  dental  disability  annuities  auto  home  other pro